 46  /-- We can forget the primality property and regard a multiset
 47   of primes as just a multiset of positive integers, or a multiset
 48   of natural numbers.  In the opposite direction, if we have a
 49   multiset of positive integers or natural numbers, together with
 50   a proof that all the elements are prime, then we can regard it
 51   as a multiset of primes.  The next block of results records
 52   obvious properties of these coercions.
 53  -/
